[2026-05-02] FinanceBench two-stage retrieval / page merge hotfix

Summary:
- Fixed two-stage retrieval so stage 2 re-searches inside selected docs with the original query instead of scanning all doc-start chunks.
- Added fallback blending: initial reranked chunks + page-stage candidates + merge-window chunks, then unified rerank.
- Added cover/TOC filtering heuristics to suppress page 0 / SEC cover / table of contents chunks for normal FinanceBench questions.
- Prevented auto-merge from collapsing final retrieved chunks far below FINANCE_RAG_FINAL_TOP_K when enough leaf chunks exist.
- Extended rag_trace and diagnostics with cover_page_filtered_count, fallback_used, final chunk count, and page-number distribution.

Files:
- backend/rag_utils.py
- backend/rag_pipeline.py
- backend/schemas.py
